BILLS BROTHERS MEMORIAL CORPORATION v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE. No. 53. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. June 9, 1930. Lindsey & Larwill, of Denver, Colo., for petitioner. C. M. Charest, Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before COTTERAL, PHILLIPS, and MeDERMOTT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Dismissed June 9, 1930, for failure diligently to proseeute.
